<BaseLayout title="About" description="What is cnjianghu? A curated cultural discovery platform for the global Chinamaxing community.">
  <div class="container-article py-16">
    <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-heading font-bold text-ink-900 dark:text-ink-50 mb-8">
      About <span class="text-vermilion">cnjianghu</span>
    </h1>

    <div class="prose dark:prose-invert">
      <p class="text-lg">
        <strong class="font-chinese">江湖</strong> <em>(jiāng hú)</em> — literally "rivers and lakes" — is one of the most evocative concepts in Chinese culture. It refers to the informal, living world that exists beneath official structures: the world of wanderers, storytellers, fighters, merchants, and everyday people navigating life on their own terms.
      </p>

      <p>
        <strong>cnjianghu</strong> borrows this spirit. We're not a textbook. We're not a news outlet. We're a curated window into the real, vibrant, messy, beautiful jianghu of Chinese culture — built for people around the world who are genuinely curious.
      </p>

      <h2>Why this exists</h2>

      <p>
        There's a growing wave of global interest in Chinese culture — sometimes called <em>Chinamaxing</em>. People are discovering Chinese food, internet culture, philosophy, aesthetics, and technology. But they hit a wall: the best content is in Chinese, scattered across dozens of platforms, and often lacks the cultural context that makes it truly understandable.
      </p>

      <p>
        cnjianghu bridges that gap. We find the most interesting, insightful, and surprising content about Chinese culture, translate it with cultural context (not just words), and present it in a way that's accessible, engaging, and respectful.
      </p>

      <h2>Our principles</h2>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Authentic over polished</strong> — Real China, not the brochure version</li>
        <li><strong>Deep over wide</strong> — We'd rather explain one thing well than skim a hundred</li>
        <li><strong>Story over fact</strong> — Knowledge sticks better when it comes with a story</li>
        <li><strong>Curiosity over pedagogy</strong> — We spark questions, not lectures</li>
        <li><strong>Insider perspective</strong> — "Come walk with us" rather than "let us tell you about"</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Who makes this</h2>

      <p>
        cnjianghu is an independent, open-source cultural project. It's built and maintained by a small team of culture enthusiasts who believe that understanding breeds connection, and connection makes the world a little better.
      </p>

      <p>
        Want to contribute, suggest content, or just say hello?
        Find us on <a href="https://github.com/Mocooa/cnjianghu">GitHub</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
